20/04/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Alpine skiing champion Janica Kostelic held a press conference Thursday (April 19th) to announce the end of her career.
The four-time Olympic gold medallist cited her numerous injuries and fears she could experience others in the future, with more serious consequences.
She has already undergone ten knee operations and thyroid surgery.
Kostelic, 25, is the most successful female skier in the world.
(Vecernji List, Vjesnik - 20/04/07;
HINA, HRT, Javno.hr, AP - 19/04/07)
